@node bugs "Bugs"
@prev authors
@next notes

The HyperHelp system was developed and tested simultaneously on the
following systems:

   * Amiga 4000/EC030
     4MB RAM
     80MB AT/IDE hardrive
     Maxon C++ 1.10.3 // SAS/C
     GoldED 0.98

   * Amiga 2000
     68030 Turboboard
     8MB ram
     200MB ALF3/SCSII harddrive
     Picasso II graphiccard
     SASC version 6.51
     CygnusED version 2.11


@{b}BugList@{ub} and @{b}Future@{ub}

(@{b}b@{ub}) represents a bug
(@{b}i@{ub}) represents a desired improvement
(@{b}u@{ub}) represents an undesirable feature (not a bug, but
almost), or an improvement that is almost required.

   (@{b}i@{ub}) Saving/Using from HyperHelp should update HyperHelp_cx
   
   (@{b}i@{ub}) Optional "load index into memory" feature.
   
   (@{b}i@{ub}) A completely GUI (~MUI) oriented Preferences program
   for those unfortunates who don't have MUI.
   
   (@{b}i@{ub}) Users should be able get a list of all guides
   currently in the index from HyperHelp.
   
   (@{b}i@{ub}) A "remove" button in the HyperHelp program for forcing
   HyperHelp_cx to quit.
   
   (@{b}u@{ub}) Clipboard support
   
   (@{b}i@{ub}) _cx control through ARexx
   
   (@{b}i@{ub}) Links to normal ASCII texts in the index
   
   (@{b}i@{ub}) Locale library support (Almost superfluous in these
   programs)

During the course of this project, we discovered a multitude of bugs
in code generated by the Maxon compiler, which caused several delays
in development. In the final phase I aquired the SAS/C package, and
developement and debugging went much more quickly. In addition, Maxon
doesn't hold to the ANSI standard too well. It's unfortunate, because
MCPPC a spicy little compiler. As it stands, MaxonC++ will not likely
be used in any future Apocalypse products (including releases of
HyperHelp).

@endnode

@node notes "General Q&A, and paradigms"
@prev bugs
@next mui

We'll try to anticipate some questions you may have, and let you know why we implemented some things the way we did.

   (@{b}Q@{ub}) Why are all of the nodes in the index file upper-case?
   (@{b}A@{ub}) This is to speed up the search routine. The speed gain
   (~12%) wasn't quite what we expected (~25%), so if you'd
   @{i}really@{ui} like to have your nodes displayed with the proper
   case, drop us a line. If we recieve enough requests we'll change it
   back.

   (@{b}Q@{ub}) Sometimes HyperHelp_cx doesn't work. Why?!?
   (@{b}A@{ub}) First, the only solution to this is to reboot. This is
   a bug in the AmigaGuide library, not in HyperHelp_cx. Please do not
   write us about this.

   (@{b}Q@{ub}) I've noticed that HyperHelp causes memory loss.
   (@{b}A@{ub}) So have we. 184 bytes per window that it opens, to be
   exact. This is a bug in the MUI library (version 7.973), not in
   HyperHelp. The author of MUI is aware of the problem and is working
   on it.


@endnode

